msgctxt "sn10.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Dutiyasukkāsutta "
msgstr "10. With the Nun Sukkā (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.213, sc1
msgctxt "sn10.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.10:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako sukkāya bhikkhuniyā bhojanaṃ adāsi. "
msgstr "Now at that time a certain lay follower gave food to the nun Sukkā. "

msgctxt "sn10.10:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sukkāya bhikkhuniyā abhippasanno yakkho rājagahe rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then a native spirit was so devoted to Sukkā that he went street to street and square to square, and on that occasion recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2, verse-num-sc844
msgctxt "sn10.10:2.1"
msgid "“Puññaṃ vata pasavi bahuṃ, "
msgstr "“O! He has made so much merit! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.10:2.2"
msgid "Sappañño vatāyaṃ upāsako; "
msgstr "That lay follower is so very wise. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.10:2.3"
msgid "Yo sukkāya adāsi bhojanaṃ, "
msgstr "He just gave food to Sukkā, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vippamuttiyā”ti → vippamuttāyāti (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn10.10:2.4"
msgid "Sabbaganthehi vippamuttiyā”ti. "
msgstr "who is released from all ties.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
